{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"mathsize","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Global_attributes/mathsize","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"\n    <ol>\n        <li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element\">MathML Reference</a></strong>\n\n        \n            </li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/maction\">&lt;maction&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/math\">&lt;math&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/menclose\">&lt;menclose&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/merror\">&lt;merror&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mfenced\">&lt;mfenced&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mfrac\">&lt;mfrac&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mi\">&lt;mi&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mmultiscripts\">&lt;mmultiscripts&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mn\">&lt;mn&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mo\">&lt;mo&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mover\">&lt;mover&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mpadded\">&lt;mpadded&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mphantom\">&lt;mphantom&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mroot\">&lt;mroot&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mrow\">&lt;mrow&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/ms\">&lt;ms&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mspace\">&lt;mspace&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/msqrt\">&lt;msqrt&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mstyle\">&lt;mstyle&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/msub\">&lt;msub&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/msubsup\">&lt;msubsup&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/msup\">&lt;msup&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mtable\">&lt;mtable&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mtd\">&lt;mtd&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mtext\">&lt;mtext&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/mtr\">&lt;mtr&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/munder\">&lt;munder&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/munderover\">&lt;munderover&gt;</a></li>\n        \n            <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Element/semantics\">&lt;semantics&gt;</a></li>\n        \n\n        \n    </ol>\n","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <strong><code>mathsize</code></strong> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Global_attributes\">global attribute</a> sets the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/font-size\">font-size</a> of a MathML element.</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect1\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> Use CSS for styling MathML whenever possible. The <code>mathsize</code> attribute should only be included for applications that are not CSS-aware and will be overridden by the CSS <code>font-size</code> property , if set.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- &lt;length&gt; values --&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>math</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">mathsize</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>12px<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>math</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">mathsize</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>0.8em<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- &lt;percentage&gt; values --&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>math</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">mathsize</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>80%<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"values","title":"Values","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"length\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length\"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>A positive <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length\"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a> value. For most font-relative units (such as <code>em</code> and <code>ex</code>), the font size is relative to the parent element's font size.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"percentage\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/percentage\"><code>&lt;percentage&gt;</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>A positive <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/percentage\"><code>&lt;percentage&gt;</code></a> value, relative to the parent element's font size.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"notes_on_mathml_versions","title":"Notes on MathML versions","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"query":"mathml.global_attributes.mathsize","specifications":[]}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>\n    In MathML 3 and earlier versions, keywords <code>small</code>, <code>normal</code>, and <code>big</code> as\n    well as the MathML3-specific syntax for lengths was supported.\n    Since MathML Core, the syntax matches CSS\n    <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length-percentage\"><code>&lt;length-percentage&gt;</code></a> values.\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    This attribute was designed for MathML applications that are not CSS-aware.\n    Since MathML Core, the use of equivalent CSS is recommended instead.\n  </li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"data":null,"query":"mathml.global_attributes.mathsize","browsers":null}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>All <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Global_attributes\">global attributes</a>.</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/font-size\"><code>font-size</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Notes on MathML versions","id":"notes_on_mathml_versions"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The mathsize global attribute sets the font-size of a MathML element.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-09T04:10:27.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/mathml/global_attributes/mathsize","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/mathml/global_attributes/mathsize/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/2039591f80b7218cbc4f5918f2a873814e83321c","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML","title":"MathML"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Global_attributes","title":"Global attributes"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/MathML/Global_attributes/mathsize","title":"mathsize"}],"pageTitle":"mathsize - MathML | MDN","noIndexing":false}}